Korean Beef Bowls
  --Myo Quinn

Beef:
4 cloves garlic, minced or finely grated
1 tsp minced or finely grated peeled ginger
3 tbsp shoyu
2 tbsp sugar
2 tbsp water
2 tsp gochujang (Korean pepper paste)
1/4 tsp freshly ground black pepper
1 tbsp neutral oil, such as canola or avocado
1 lb lean ground beef
1 tbsp toasted sesame seeds
1 tsp toasted sesame oil

Stir garlic cloves, ginger, shoyu, sugar, water, gochujang, and pepper together in a small bowl. Heat oil in a large 12" skillet over medium-high heat until shimmering. Add ground beef and cook, breaking up the meat into small pieces, until browned, ~6 min. Stir in the sauce and cook until it evenly coats the beef, ~1 min. Turn off the heat. Stir in toasted sesame seeds and toasted sesame oil.

Bowls:
4 c hot cooked white rice
1/2 medium English cucumber, thinly sliced crosswise (~1 c)
1 medium carrot, peeled and shredded (~1 c)
1/4 small red or green cabbage, shredded (~2 c)
1 medium scallion, thinly sliced (~1/4 c)

Divide 4 rice between 4 bowls. Divide the beef over the rice. Divide cucumber, carrot, red cabbage, scallion between the bowls. 


Notes: The sauce can be made 1 day ahead and refrigerated until ready to use.


